The South African Air Force showcased the operational readiness of its fighter jets and helicopters at the Roodewal Weapons Range, located near Air Force Base Makhado in Limpopo. Photojournalist Tebogo Letsiecaptured the demonstration, aimed at reflecting the air forceâ€™s capability when it comes to precision attacks, low-level reconnaissance, combat search and rescue, dive-bombing and various other airlift and shooting exercises in a typical wartime scenario. The show was repeated at the Africa Aerospace and Defence air show and exhibition at Waterkloof in Pretoria.  